definition.value: A food product made from the fruiting body of a subterranean ascomycete fungus, predominantly one of the many species of the genus Tuber.
A food product made from black, white, pink or similar peppercorns.
A food product made from tonka beans
A food product made from the tamarillo fruit.
A dual purpose medium to large drupe or stone fruit of the Olea europea tree used as table olives and for olive oil production
Juice from white grapefruit
A type of drop cookie distinguished by an oatmeal-based dough with raisins mixed throughout.
A tomato sauce, usually made with tomatoes, garlic, herbs, and onions. Its many variations can include the addition of capers, olives, spices, and a dash of wine.
A dish flavoured with sweet and sour sauce, and having vegetables and/or animal meat.
A sausage made from turkey meat
Roasted sunflower seeds with shell removed

A class of tomatoes believed to be of southeast Asian origin, shaped similarly to the oval plum tomatoes but having the small size and sweetness of cherry tomatoes. Grape tomatoes produce small and typically oblong fruits.
A sweet and sour sauce dish having pork as a defining ingredient.
A beef primal cut that comes from the area below the backbone .
A portion of meat from either the short loin, the sirloin, or the tenderloin muscle area.

The area below the backbone is home to some of the most tender and popular cuts of beef, such as the Tenderloin, Strip Steak, T-Bone and Porterhouse Steaks. Loin cuts are exceptionally prepared on the grill or under a broiler.
A cut of beef corresponding to the psoas major muscle, which is very tender.
A boneless steak cut from the sirloin region
A beef steak that is prepared from the beef short loin. The maximum width of the tenderloin must be at least 1/2 inch (13mm) when measured parallel to the length of the backbone.
A steak of beef cut from the front of the short loin area.
The name originates from the characteristic T-shape of its bone.
A beef steak that is prepared from the beef short loin. The maximum width of the tenderloin must be atleast 1.25 inches (3.2cm) when measured parallel to the length of the backbone.
A steak of beef cut from the back of the short loin area.
Differentiated from the T-Bone steak by its larger Tenderloin muscle.
Flour ground from blue flint corn.
A process which separates a culinary nut's shell from its meat, leaving the meat part more or less intact.
A pod from a winged bean plant.
The tender pods, which are the most widely eaten part of the plant, are best when eaten before they exceed 2.5 cm (1.0 in) in length.[Wikipedia]
A dog treat consisting of an animal bone with or without tendon or other tissue.
A dog chew made out of rawhide.
A large cat native to the mountain ranges of Central and South Asia.
A group of indeterminate heirloom tomatoes in the shape of a pear, but smaller, and having yellow, orange, and red varieties.
A food product based on a group of beans distinguished by their white skin.
A pea variety that yeilds green-colored seeds at maturity.

A type of coarse-ground whole wheat flour similar to conventional whole wheat flour in that both are made from the whole grain, but graham flour is ground more coarsely and is not sifted during milling (i.e. unbolted).

In the United States, a langostino lobster food product is legislated to refer to one of three species of squat lobster in the family Galatheidae: Cervimunida johni, Munida gregaria, and Pleuroncodes monodon.
A lemon, whole or in pieces, for eating or other food processing.
A food product derived from yuzu fruit
A whole raw yuzu fruit
A hesperidium fruit of a citrus plant (Citrus).
A thigh poultry cut of turkey
A whole thigh that is obtained from a turkey.
A sandwich containing peanut butter as a defining ingredient.
A hind limb poultry cut of a turkey
A whole leg that is obtained from a turkey.
A turkey thigh that contains skin.
A turkey thigh that still contains the skin.
A skinless turkey thigh.
A turkey thigh after the skin has been removed.
A chicken thigh that contains skin.
A chicken thigh that still contains the skin.
A skinless chicken thigh.
An adult female swine.
A portion of a food product presented in the general context of daily a recommended intake of a food group.
A specific amount of food that a food product's nutrition facts' listed nutrient quantities pertain to.
An amount of a specific food an individual eats for dinner, snack, or other eating occasion.
A percentage indicating how much a nutrient in a single serving of an individual packaged food or dietary supplement contributes to an individual's recommended daily value intake for that nutrient.
A datum about a recommended amount of a nutrient for an individual to consume or not to exceed each day.
